WEBVTT

00:00.280 --> 00:01.580
Do you know...
知道么…

00:01.640 --> 00:05.740
that the only dog ever struck by lightning was right here, in Egypt?
史上唯一一只被闪电击中的狗就在埃及？

00:07.700 --> 00:11.900
I wish I'd met you before we were dead.
真希望我能在死之前遇见你

00:16.160 --> 00:19.440
You know, technically...
从理论上讲…

00:21.320 --> 00:23.760
we could cross off two items:
我们一次实现了两项愿望

00:24.360 --> 00:26.180
"See the pyramids"...
看看金字塔

00:28.040 --> 00:30.540
and "witness something majestic."
以及"亲眼目睹神迹"

00:31.500 --> 00:34.660
This is about as majestic as it gets.
眼前的奇观已经近乎神迹了

00:36.080 --> 00:37.600
Wait till you see my mountain.
等你看到我的神山再说吧

00:38.300 --> 00:39.600
Oh, yeah.
哦 是啊

00:41.820 --> 00:43.120
Your mountain.
你的神山

00:45.120 --> 00:48.880
Still, this ain't half bad.
这个已经非常不错了

00:49.220 --> 00:52.680
You know, the ancient Egyptians had a beautiful belief about death.
知道么 古埃及人对死亡有种美好的信念

00:54.180 --> 00:58.220
When their souls got to the entrance to heaven, the gods asked them two questions.
当他们的灵魂到了天堂门口, 他们的神们会问他们两个问题

00:59.440 --> 01:02.300
Their answers determined whether they were admitted or not.
天堂的门是否开放 取决于问题的答案

01:04.300 --> 01:07.800
Okay, I'll bite.
好吧 我来试试

01:09.440 --> 01:11.100
What were they?
是什么问题？

01:12.920 --> 01:15.640
Have you found joy in your life?
在你的生命中 是否有过快乐？

01:21.100 --> 01:22.460
Answer the question.
回答我

01:22.900 --> 01:27.120
- Me? - Yeah, you. - Answer the question, "Have I found joy in my life?" - Yes.
- 我么？- 是的 就是你。 - 问题是"我的生命中有没有快乐？" - 没错

01:31.540 --> 01:32.460
Yes.
有

01:33.400 --> 01:36.020
Has your life brought joy to others?
那你这一生有没有给别人带去快乐？

01:38.200 --> 01:40.760
Ah, this type of question, I...
呃 这样的问题 我…

01:41.720 --> 01:43.980
I don't know, uh...
我不知道…

01:44.300 --> 01:47.300
I don't think about how other people gauge, uh...
不知别人心里是怎么想的 所以…

01:49.720 --> 01:51.400
Ask them.
问他们去吧

01:51.400 --> 01:52.760
I'm asking you.
我问的是你

01:56.940 --> 01:57.680
Fine.
好罢

01:59.840 --> 02:00.840
Fine.
好罢

